The paper focuses on analyzing the behavior of evolving systems through the lens of dynamic networks, which falls under the scope of social networks (cs.SOC) and data science (cs.DS). The proposed method involves characterizing individual nodes based on the evolution of their direct neighborhood, which is a common approach in network analysis (cs.SI). The paper also applies frequent pattern mining and cluster analysis, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS).
